==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scripturist
<hw>Scrip"tur*ist</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is
strongly attached to, or versed in, the Scriptures, or who endeavors to
regulate his life by them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Puritan was a <qex>Scripturist</qex>, -- a
<qex>Scripturist</qex> with all his heart, if as yet with imperfect
intelligence . . . he cherished the scheme of looking to the Word of God
as his sole and universal directory.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrit</ent>⟦br⟧
